title: Dead_End_(1937)_William_Wyler_mkv_tsantilas
description:
Dead End is a 1937 crime drama film. It is an adaptation of the Sidney Kingsley 1935 Broadway play of the same name. The play was adapted by Lillian Hellman. It stars Humphrey Bogart, Joel McCrea, and Sylvia Sidney. It is notable as being the first film appearance of the Dead End Kids. 

Plot: The Dead End Kids are introduced in their intricate East Side slum, overlooked by the apartments of the rich. Their antics, some funny, some vicious, alternate with subplots: unemployed architect Dave (Joel McCrea) is torn between Drina (Silvia Sidney), sweet but equally poor, and Kay (Wendy Barrie), a rich man's mistress; gangster Baby Face Martin (Humphrey Bogart) returns to his old neighborhood and finds that nobody is glad to see him. Then violent crime, both juvenile and adult, impacts the neighborhood and its people.
